Business Brief -- Martin Lawrence Limited Editions:
   Pretax Gain of $1.5 Million
   To Be Posted for 1st Period
Martin Lawrence, based in Van Nuys, Calif., filed a suit
against Mr. Yamagata a year ago, charging breach of contract.
Mr. Yamagata then filed a cross-complaint. As part of the
resolved dispute, the parties said they are ending their
business relationship. Martin Lawrence also agreed to give up
rights it claimed to certain of Mr. Yamagata's artwork and
said it will return some of his other works that it had
planned to publish and sell.
   Martin Lawrence stock was quoted at $2, unchanged, in late
New York Stock Exchange trading Friday.